> how will you analyze logs, do you know any commands to list logs to...:

    - basically, to analyze logs, i follow a step-by-step approach

    - first, i identify the correct log file location, which could be application
      logs or system logs

    - then, instead of opening the entire file, i use commands to filter and view relevant data

    - for example, i use tail -f <logifle> to monitor logs in realtime

    - if i want to search for specific error, i use grep like grep -e error which help in quickly identifying issues

    - from i use head and tail to view the beginning or end of the logs

